  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DR Congo, Ituri province: Monitoring security incidents and human rights</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity building of PAX partners in the Eastern DR Congo showed the added value within the cooperation between PAX and AINL. In 2017, three PAX partners from Ituri Province conducted an exchange visit to Amnesty partners in North Kivu and were subsequently trained by Amnesty in both 2017 and 2018 in security monitoring and reporting. Strengthened skills then allowed these three partners to build the capacities of local peace committees so that they could document security incidents and raise them with local authorities. As a result, local bodies in Ituri Province had become more skilled, active and self-confident in their advocacy for issues in their interest with local and intermediary-level (security) authorities. They ensured that authorities got monthly updates on security incidents from the areas they covered.</narrative>
  </description>
